        , 29: [ {class: "vs", text: "And as I was speaking these words, behold, the angel who had come to me at the first came to me, and he looked upon me:"} ]
        , 30: [ {class: "vs", text: "and, behold, I lay as one that had been dead, and my understanding was taken from me; and he took me by the right hand, and comforted me, and set me upon my feet, and said to me,"} ]
        , 31: [ {class: "vs", text: "What ails you? and why are you so disquieted? and why is your understanding troubled, and the thoughts of your heart?"} ]
        , 32: [ {class: "vs", text: "And I said, Because you have forsaken me: yet I did according to your words, and went into the field, and, behold, I have seen, and yet see, that which I am not able to express."} ]
